<figureCitation id="1375F6C0FFC09E1E832322B73BB04AC5" box="[617,704,914,940]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="11.[136,229,1736,1758]" captionTargetBox="[341,1247,190,1712]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[340,1247,190,1712]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 3. Species of Gentianaceae from the Parque Municipal de Mucugê - Projeto Sempre Viva (PMM), Bahia, Brazil: Calolisianthus pedunculatus (A), Chelonanthus purpurascens (B), Curtia verticillaris (C), Curtia tenuifolia (D), Prepusa montana (E), Schultesia bahiensis (F), Schultesia crenuliflora (G), Schultesia pachyphylla (H). Scale bars:A: 2 cm; B: 1 cm; C: 0,5 cm; D: 0,5 cm; E: 2 cm; F–H: 1 cm. Photo A, B, E, F, G and H by Maria Luiza Silveira de Carvalho; C and D by Vinicius Dittrich and Gustavo Shimizu, respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5424491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5424491/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF1EA45FFC09E1E81C222FF38894DA5" blockId="12.[136,1452,986,1624]" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC09E1E81C222FF39BC4A9D" box="[136,204,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Herbs</emphasis>
, 
<quantity id="4CB647A0FFC09E1E819322FF38374A9D" box="[217,327,986,1012]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" unit="cm" value="45.0" valueMax="70.0" valueMin="20.0">20–70 cm</quantity>
tall. 
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC09E1E803722FF38974A9D" box="[381,487,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Branches</emphasis>
green or vinaceous, cylindrical, costate. 
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC09E1E82E322FE3A874A9D" box="[937,1015,987,1012]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Leaves</emphasis>
verticillate, sessile, discolorous, blades 7.2–9.8 × 
<quantity id="4CB647A0FFC09E1E81B222DB38F04D71" box="[248,384,1022,1049]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.5" valueMin="1.5">1.5–3.5 mm</quantity>
, elliptical, chartaceous, glabrous, attenuate at base, acute at apex, entire at margin. 
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC09E1E845C22DB3CDC4D71" box="[1302,1452,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Inflorescence</emphasis>
in terminal biparous cyme, multiflora; peduncle 
<quantity id="4CB647A0FFC09E1E83F025073A7D4D55" box="[698,781,1058,1085]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.9" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" unit="cm" value="5.9">5.9 cm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC09E1E825125073A074D55" box="[795,887,1058,1084]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Flowers</emphasis>
homostylous, 5-merous, pedicel ca. 
<quantity id="4CB647A0FFC09E1E846825073C104D55" box="[1314,1376,1058,1084]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" unit="cm" value="3.0">3 cm</quantity>
; calyx 0.3–4.3 × 
<quantity id="4CB647A0FFC09E1E81B0256338F34D09" box="[250,387,1094,1120]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="16.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="0.85" valueMax="1.6" valueMin="0.1">0.1–1.6 mm</quantity>
, green to vinaceous, keeled, not winged, tubular, glabrous; corolla, yellowish, purplish or pink, tubular to campanulate, tube 0.9–2.3 × 1.0- 
<quantity id="4CB647A0FFC09E1E8336254F3BB04DED" box="[636,704,1130,1156]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
, lobes 3.3 × 
<quantity id="4CB647A0FFC09E1E8213254F3AC34DED" box="[857,947,1130,1156]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="0.8">0.8 mm</quantity>
, lanceolate to ovate, at apex acute; stamens ca. 
<quantity id="4CB647A0FFC09E1E81FA25AB39834DC1" box="[176,243,1166,1192]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
, isodynamous, adnate, conation 
<quantity id="4CB647A0FFC09E1E832825AB3BA64DC1" box="[610,726,1166,1193]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.0">1–1.5 mm</quantity>
, anthers basifixed; ovary 
<quantity id="4CB647A0FFC09E1E82B225AB3DF24DC1" box="[1016,1154,1166,1192]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.65" metricValueMax="3.6" metricValueMin="1.7" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="2.65" valueMax="3.6" valueMin="1.7">1.7–3.6 mm</quantity>
, style 
<quantity id="4CB647A0FFC09E1E858125AB3C244DC1" box="[1227,1364,1166,1192]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.05" metricValueMax="3.4" metricValueMin="0.7" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="2.05" valueMax="3.4" valueMin="0.7">0.7–3.4 mm</quantity>
, stigma bilobed. 
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC09E1E81A0259638544DA5" box="[234,292,1203,1228]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Fruit</emphasis>
septicidal capsule.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C354B9CEFFC09E1E81F725F03DE84C51" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BF1EA45FFC09E1E81F725F03DE84C51" blockId="12.[136,1452,986,1624]" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC09E1E81F725F038984D86" bold="true" box="[189,488,1237,1264]" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Habitat and distribution</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E91C6FFC09E1E834125F33B914D99" authorityName="Knoblauch" authorityYear="1894" box="[523,737,1238,1264]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gentianaceae" genus="Curtia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verticillaris">
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC09E1E834125F33B914D99" box="[523,737,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Curtia verticillaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingCountry id="F359AAD5FFC09E1E82DA25F33AA44D99" box="[912,980,1238,1264]" name="Brazil" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and is distributed in the states of 
<collectingRegion id="498A24A7FFC09E1E842925F33CD74D99" box="[1379,1447,1238,1264]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="498A24A7FFC09E1E81C225DF384E4C7D" box="[136,318,1274,1300]" country="Brazil" name="Distrito Federal" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Distrito Federal</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="498A24A7FFC09E1E800025DF38FB4C7D" box="[330,395,1274,1300]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Goiás</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="498A24A7FFC09E1E808C25DF3B2E4C7D" box="[454,606,1274,1300]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFDF97B4FFC09E1E832525DF3A174C7D" author="Bissoli, V. F. &amp; Calio, M. F." box="[623,871,1274,1300]" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" refId="ref12583" refString="Bissoli, V. F. &amp; Calio, M. F. (2020) Curtia in Flora do Brasil 2020. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Avilable from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / reflora / floradobrasil / FB 7757 (accessed 30 November 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Bissoli &amp; Calió 2020</bibRefCitation>
), places that contains “campo rupestre” (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDF97B4FFC09E1E847125DF38D84C51" author="Crespo, S. R. M. &amp; Marcondes-Ferreira, W." pageId="12" pageNumber="73" pagination="423 - 444" refId="ref13891" refString="Crespo, S. R. M. &amp; Marcondes-Ferreira, W. (2009) Revisao taxonomica do genero Curtia (Gentianaceae). Rodriguesia 60: 423 - 444. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / 2175 - 7860200960214" type="journal article" year="2009">Crespo &amp; Marcondes-Ferreira 2009</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDF97B4FFC09E1E80F9243B3BE24C51" author="Siqueira, G. B. &amp; Espirito Santo, F. B. &amp; Rapini, A." box="[435,658,1310,1336]" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref17510" refString="Siqueira, G. B., Espirito Santo, F. B. &amp; Rapini, A. (2014) Flora da Bahia: Gentianaceae. Sitientibus serie Ciencias Biologicas 14: 1 - 33. https: // doi. org / 10.13102 / scb 295" type="journal article" year="2014">
Siqueira 
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC09E1E8352243A3B204C51" box="[536,592,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDF97B4FFC09E1E83D7243B3AFC4C51" author="Bissoli, V. F. &amp; Calio, M. F." box="[669,908,1310,1336]" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" refId="ref12583" refString="Bissoli, V. F. &amp; Calio, M. F. (2020) Curtia in Flora do Brasil 2020. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Avilable from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / reflora / floradobrasil / FB 7757 (accessed 30 November 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Bissoli &amp; Calió 2020</bibRefCitation>
) (
<figureCitation id="1375F6C0FFC09E1E82E9243B3A8A4C51" box="[931,1018,1310,1336]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="11.[136,229,1736,1758]" captionTargetBox="[341,1247,190,1712]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[340,1247,190,1712]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 3. Species of Gentianaceae from the Parque Municipal de Mucugê - Projeto Sempre Viva (PMM), Bahia, Brazil: Calolisianthus pedunculatus (A), Chelonanthus purpurascens (B), Curtia verticillaris (C), Curtia tenuifolia (D), Prepusa montana (E), Schultesia bahiensis (F), Schultesia crenuliflora (G), Schultesia pachyphylla (H). Scale bars:A: 2 cm; B: 1 cm; C: 0,5 cm; D: 0,5 cm; E: 2 cm; F–H: 1 cm. Photo A, B, E, F, G and H by Maria Luiza Silveira de Carvalho; C and D by Vinicius Dittrich and Gustavo Shimizu, respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5424491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5424491/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
, Appendix 1).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C354B9CEFFC09E1E81F724643DA04F31" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF1EA45FFC09E1E81F7246439854CA1" blockId="12.[136,1452,986,1624]" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC09E1E81F72464384E4C32" bold="true" box="[189,318,1345,1371]" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Comments</emphasis>
:—Leaves of this species vary in height, color and size among the individuals. In addition, homostylous flowers of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E91C6FFC09E1E804B244338A54CE9" authorityName="Knoblauch" authorityYear="1894" box="[257,469,1382,1408]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gentianaceae" genus="Curtia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verticillaris">
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC09E1E804B244338A54CE9" box="[257,469,1382,1408]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Curtia verticillaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the tristylous flowers of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E91C6FFC09E1E823024433D464CE9" authorityName="Knoblauch" authorityYear="1894" box="[890,1078,1382,1408]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gentianaceae" genus="Curtia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tenuifolia">
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC09E1E823024433D464CE9" box="[890,1078,1382,1408]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Curtia tenuifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as mentioned above (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDF97B4FFC09E1E847B244339994CCD" author="Siqueira, G. B. &amp; Espirito Santo, F. B. &amp; Rapini, A." pageId="12" pageNumber="73" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref17510" refString="Siqueira, G. B., Espirito Santo, F. B. &amp; Rapini, A. (2014) Flora da Bahia: Gentianaceae. Sitientibus serie Ciencias Biologicas 14: 1 - 33. https: // doi. org / 10.13102 / scb 295" type="journal article" year="2014">
Siqueira 
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC09E1E84DD244239D54CCD" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
). Can be found with flowers and fruits throughout the year (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDF97B4FFC09E1E82DA24AF3C574CCD" author="Crespo, S. R. M. &amp; Marcondes-Ferreira, W." box="[912,1319,1418,1444]" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" pagination="423 - 444" refId="ref13891" refString="Crespo, S. R. M. &amp; Marcondes-Ferreira, W. (2009) Revisao taxonomica do genero Curtia (Gentianaceae). Rodriguesia 60: 423 - 444. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / 2175 - 7860200960214" type="journal article" year="2009">Crespo &amp; Marcondes-Ferreira 2009</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDF97B4FFC09E1E847824AF39994CA1" author="Siqueira, G. B. &amp; Espirito Santo, F. B. &amp; Rapini, A." pageId="12" pageNumber="73" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref17510" refString="Siqueira, G. B., Espirito Santo, F. B. &amp; Rapini, A. (2014) Flora da Bahia: Gentianaceae. Sitientibus serie Ciencias Biologicas 14: 1 - 33. https: // doi. org / 10.13102 / scb 295" type="journal article" year="2014">
Siqueira 
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC09E1E84DD24AE39D54CA1" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
